Sentencas: Y0.5Ca0.5-xInxBaCo3.2Ga0.8O7+delta (x = 0.0 or 0.1, and denoted as YCBCG, YCIBCG, respectively) oxides are synthesized and investigated as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Phase stability and electrochemical performance of Y0.5Ca0.5-xInxBaCo3.2Ga0.8O7+δ (x=0 and 0.1) as cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The In content (x) significantly affects the properties of Y0.5Ca0.5-xInxBaCo3.2Ga0.8O7+delta.
Titulo: Phase stability and electrochemical performance of Y0.5Ca0.5-xInxBaCo3.2Ga0.8O7+δ (x=0 and 0.1) as cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The YCIBCG oxide exhibit superior phase stability compared to YCBCG at high temperatures (700-950 degrees C).
Titulo: Phase stability and electrochemical performance of Y0.5Ca0.5-xInxBaCo3.2Ga0.8O7+δ (x=0 and 0.1) as cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The substitution of In for Ca improves the long-term phase stability at higher temperatures, but slightly degrades the electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Phase stability and electrochemical performance of Y0.5Ca0.5-xInxBaCo3.2Ga0.8O7+δ (x=0 and 0.1) as cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) values of the YCBCG and YCIBCG oxides are 9.8 x 10(-6) K-1 and 9.7 x 10(-6) K-1 in the range of 30-850 degrees C, respectively, which provides good mechanical compatibility with the electrolyte (10.9 x 10(-6) K-1 for LSGM).
Titulo: Phase stability and electrochemical performance of Y0.5Ca0.5-xInxBaCo3.2Ga0.8O7+δ (x=0 and 0.1) as cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The interfacial polarization resistances for YCBCG and YCIBCG cathode are as low as 0.140 Omega cm(2) and 0.146 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Phase stability and electrochemical performance of Y0.5Ca0.5-xInxBaCo3.2Ga0.8O7+δ (x=0 and 0.1) as cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power densities of the NiO-SDC/SDC/LSGM/YCBCG and NiO-SDC/SDC/LSGM/YCIBCG cells are 434 and 415 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C, respectively with a 300 mu m thick electrolyte.
Titulo: Phase stability and electrochemical performance of Y0.5Ca0.5-xInxBaCo3.2Ga0.8O7+δ (x=0 and 0.1) as cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results of this study demonstrate that YCBCG and YCIBCG are very promising cathode materials for intermediate temperature SOFCs.
Titulo: Phase stability and electrochemical performance of Y0.5Ca0.5-xInxBaCo3.2Ga0.8O7+δ (x=0 and 0.1) as cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
